PRDM14 Gene Expression Analysis Code

This file contains the code used analyze the DataSet_01_045.txt file, which was downloaded from https://bio.liclab.net/KnockTFv2/download.php (search GSE22795). This dataset contains gene expression data from a study that investigated the gene changes after PRDM14 knockdown in human embryonic stem cells (hESCs).

The heatmap shows the genes with the top 50 smallest adjusted p-values. A smaller adjusted p-value represents a greater statistical significance in the change in gene expression.

# define function to calculate z-score
calculate_zscore <- function(x) {
  (x - mean(x)) / sd(x)
}

# calculate z-score for each gene
zscore  <- t(apply(normal_counts, 1, calculate_zscore))

zscore_top <- zscore[top50,]

# heatmap
pheatmap(zscore_top, cluster_rows = TRUE, show_rownames = TRUE, cluster_cols = TRUE, annotation_col = coldata, main = "Heatmap of Top 50 Genes (Z-score)")

A z-score represents a genes expression level compared to the mean expression level. A positive z-score indicates that the gene expression is upregulated, and a negative z-score indicates that the gene expression is downregulated. The heatmap shows that the genes with the top 50 smallest adjusted p-values are upregulated in the treatment group (PRDM14 knockdown) compared to the control group.
